	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Farming Spirocs<BR>
<BR>
For those that have never been to Air (and I'll admit I'm no seasoned vetran), the spawns here are all very triggered, and are different than normall areas of Norrath.<BR>
<BR>
One such abnormality exsist on the Spiroc Isle. There are 11 Spirocs on this isle. They break down like this<BR>
<BR>
6 Various types (pawns if you will)<BR>
3 Vanquishers<BR>
1 Guardian<BR>
1 Lord<BR>
<BR>
Everthing is linked to its previous counterpart, and, assuming you are trying to clear the isle, you have to kill them in order. Let me explain further.<BR>
<BR>
The Vanquishers are all seperated, and each vanquisher has 2 of the &quot;pawns&quot; with it. If you kill the pawns before you kill the vanquisher, the pawns respawn instantly at their starting point.<BR>
<BR>
The guardian works a similar way with the Lord. If you kill the lord before you kill the guardian, the lord instantly respawns. Again, assuming you are just being normal, and just trying to clear the island, there isn't any way you could really get to the lord without pulling the guardian first. But, lets say you wanted to farm the guardian for the quest pieces he drops (inlcuding one for he warrior epic), you pretty much keep clear all the others on the isle, pull the guardian away from the lord and keep him mezzed, then pull the lord to your fighting area. After the lord dies, he respawns instantly. <BR>
<BR>
Rinse, Lather, Repeat.<BR>
<BR>
(p.s. I got this info from people who have been to Air more than I have, and a post from the Safehouse.)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
