			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Seems every new piece of armor that appears, some incredibly well informed wise #@$ says its fake.  Well here's the real deal.  If you have not been to the plane of sky....shut up.  In the quest section of the PoS, you take to the first efreeti to come to.  Last name is Blademaster...can't remember his first name.  Anyway, he will ask you if you are a true warrior and of course you say &quot;I am a true warrior.&quot;.  He will ask who you want summoned to test you, Falorn or Ogog.  Falorn is a Barbarian warrior and Ogog is a troll warrior.  After you say which you want summoned he gives you book to read and return to him.  Falorn's book is a neat little story about his life and Ogog's is one page of Troll gibberish talk about how good of a barsher he is.  You return the book to the Efreeti and whichever you picked is summoned.  Each gives three tests.  Ogog gives the test of Bash, Smash, and Think.  You tell him &quot; I do think test.&quot; and he gives you the quest for the belt of the four winds.  I have no idea what the stats are except that it is supposed to have a very good haste effect.  So before you jump a shout &quot;It's FAKE&quot;, please have at least some clue as to what your talking about.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quizath Silvermane<BR>
